owl:Ontology.dc:description: An ontology that describes the Genome Variation Format Version 1 (GVF) by Karen Eilbeck, Paul Flicek, Gabor Marth, Martin Reese, Lincoln Stein and Mark Yandell (http://www.sequenceontology.org/resources/gvf.html). The ontology was inspired by previous work of Robert Hoehndorf's RDF2OWL (http://code.google.com/p/rdf2owl).
owl:Ontology.dc:title: Genomic Variation Format Version 1 Ontology (GVF1O)
owl:Ontology.dc:creator: Joachim Baran

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: strand
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Strand of the feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: attributes
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Tag name/value pair attributes of a feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: parent
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Link out to the parent feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: contains
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relationship that describes which features belong to a feature set.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: region
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: FALDO "Region" instance replacement for a feature's start, stop, strand properties.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: species
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: NCBI Taxonomy Ontology "NCBITaxon_1" (or sub-classes) instance that denotes the species for a feature set.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variant
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Specific information about the variant(s) of a feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: individual
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Links to information about an individual.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: zygosity
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Zygosity of a variant.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: effect
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: An effect of a particular feature variant.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sequence_variant
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Effect of a sequence alteration on a sequence feature.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: feature_type
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A term that is describing the sequence feature that is being affected.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: feature_id
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Features that are affected by this sequence alteration effect.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: start_range
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A coordinate range for ambiguous start coordinates.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: end_range
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A coordinate range for ambiguous start coordinates.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: chromosome
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Denotes abstract chromosome representations for capturing variants that appear on the same chromosome of a polyploid organism.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: genotype
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Determines the genotype as observed in an individual.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: feature_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Feature class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: sequencedindividual_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with SequencedIndividual class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: set_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Set class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: variant_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Variant class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: effect_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Effect class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: breakpoint_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Breakpoint class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: dbxref
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A database cross-reference to associate a sequence alteration to its representation in another database.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: region
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: FALDO "Region" instance replacement for a breakpoint's start, stop, strand properties.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: breakpoint
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Potential source or destination of zero-length sequence alterations.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: strand
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Strand of the breakpoint.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: target_properties
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Target class instances.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: region
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: FALDO "Region" instance replacement for a target's start, stop, strand properties.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: strand
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Strand of a target -- if applicable.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: seqid
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: ID of the landmark that establishes the coordinate system for a feature.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: source
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A free text qualifier that describes the algorithm or operating procedure that generated this feature. For example, the name of the software that generated this feature or a database name.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: type
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Type of the feature, which is either a term from the "lite" version of the Sequence Ontology (SOFA), a term from the full Sequence Ontology (SO) that is a child of sequence_feature (SO:0000110), or a SOFA or SO accession number.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Start coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: score
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Score of the feature. For example, an E-value for sequence similarity features or a P-value for ab initio gene prediction features.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: tag
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Tag name of a feature attribute.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gvf_version
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version of the GVF specification that defines the feature set contents.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: build
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of a genome assembly build that denotes the provenance of features in a feature set. For example, 'NCBI 36' or 'FlyBase r4.1'.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_seq
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: All sequence variations at a locus -- including the reference sequence when appropriate (for example, when the locus is heterozygous). If the feature is on the minus strand, then the sequence is the reverse-compliment of the reference genome for these coordinates.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: id
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A unique identifier for the feature within the feature set.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: alias
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Secondary name of a feature, which can be HGVS/ISCN nomenclature names, but not cross-references to databases (e.g. dbSNP, OMIM) which should use the dbxref property.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: name
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Name of an external database. For example, "dbSNP" or "OMIM".

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: xref
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: External database identifier. For example, for dbSNP, this identifier could be "rs3131969".

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: reference_seq
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sequence from the reference genome.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_reads
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Number of reads that are supporting this variant.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: total_reads
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Total number of reads.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_freq
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Frequency of a variant in a population.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A coordinate that defines the start of an ambiguous coordinate range.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: A coordinate that defines the end of an ambiguous coordinate range.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: phased
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Unclear from GVF specification.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_codon
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the codon that overlaps this variant.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: reference_codon
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Describes the codon from the reference sequence whose coordinates overlap with this variant.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_aa
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Amino acid that overlaps with the variant.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: reference_aa
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Amino acid in the reference genome that overlaps with a variant's genome coordinates.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: feature_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Feature class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: variant_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Variant class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: range_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Range class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: dbxref_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with DBXRef class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: set_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Set class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: attribute_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Attribute class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: sequencedindividual_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with SequencedIndividual class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: breakpoint_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Breakpoint class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: seqid
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: ID of the landmark that establishes the coordinate system for a breakpoint.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Start coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End coordinate of the feature on the seqid landmark.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: 5'_context
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sequence context (positive strand) of a feature on the 5' end.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: 3'_context
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sequence context (positive strand) of a feature on the 3' end.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: gff_version
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Version of the GFF specification that defines the feature set contents apart from GVF related definitions.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: file_date
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Creation date of the GVF file that this set stems from.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: target_properties
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Properties that are directly associated with Target class instances.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: target_id
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: ID or accession of the target alignment.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: start
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Start coordinate of the target.

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: End coordinate of the target.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Set
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Set of genomic sequence features, whose identifiers are unique within the set.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Strand
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Class describing a genomic strand. Instances of the class (individuals) are used to denote forward-/reverse-strands, etc.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: DBXRef
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A class describing relationships between features and external databases.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Variant
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describing specific alterations of a feature.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: SequencedIndividual
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Aggregated sequencing information for a particular individual.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Effect
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describing the effect of a feature variant.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Range
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describe ambiguity in either start or end coordinates.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Chromosome
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An abstract representation of a chromosome to represent ploidy.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Breakpoint
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes the source or destination of a zero-length sequence alteration.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Target
owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates a feature's "target" of a nucleotide-to-nucleotide or protein-to-nucleotide alignment.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: UnknownStrand
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Strand was not determined, which leaves it open whether the location is on the positive (forward) or negative (reverse) strand.
